title: Two children injured after 10m balcony plunge
text:
Share on Twitter 
TWO young children were treated by paramedics after falling from a balcony in the city’s west this morning. 
A five-year-old girl and two-year-old boy fell from a balcony on South Terrace in Bankstown just before 9am. 
Emergency services were called to the property with reports the children had fallen about 10m. One of the children is raced from the building by paramedics. Picture: Channel 7 Source: Channel 7 Residents of the apartment complex look on as emergency services arrive. Picture: Channel 7 Source: Channel 7 The pair have been taken to hospital but suffered no obvious injuries. Picture: Channel 7 Source: Channel 7 
An Ambulance NSW spokesman said one of the children has been taken to The Children’s Hospital at Westmead with no obvious injuries. 
The other child is still being treated by paramedics at the scene.
